MPs warn the president of “a full-blown revolt will be inevitable” if he ignores their grievances.MPs also dismiss President Kenyatta’s BBI meeting planned for tomorrow at Sagana State Lodge.  Some 41 MPs from Mt Kenya allied to Deputy President William Ruto yesterday fired a stinging letter to President Kenyatta, warning him they will not back ODM leader Raila Odinga for the presidency.
They declared they “cannot sell Mr Odinga in the region, or any other imposed presidential candidate” and warned the president “a full-blown revolt will be inevitable” if he ignores their grievances.



